name: Slayer ring
column2: An equipable ring that provides all the functions of an Enchanted gem, and provides 8 charges for teleporting to useful Slayer sites.

name: Broad bolts
column2: Bolts that can damage Turoths and Kurask. Level 55 Slayer and 61 Ranged, alongside a suitable crossbow, are required to fire these bolts.

name: Broad arrows
column2: Arrows that can damage Turoths and Kurask. Level 55 Slayer and 50 Ranged, alongside a suitable bow, are required to fire these arrows.

name: Herb sack
column2: Stores up to 30 of each type of grimy herb (for a total of 420 herbs). Level 58 Herblore is required to use it.

name: Rune pouch
column2: Stores up to 16,000 of three types of runes. Only one can be owned. Can also be obtained by exchanging a rune pouch note at a bank.

name: Looting bag
column2: Within the Wilderness and certain other PvP areas, tradeable items can be stored in the looting bag, enabling you to carry more loot.

name: Void Knights' Reward Options#Herb pack
column2:
Contains a random assortment of noted grimy herbs.
Unlike the Nightmare Zone, these herb packs can be bought by ironmen.

name: Void Knights' Reward Options#Mineral pack
column2: Contains 25 noted coal and 18 noted iron ore.

name: Void Knights' Reward Options#Seed pack
column2: Contains a random amount of seeds, typically giving lower-tiered seeds.

name: Void knight mace
column2: Can cast and autocast Claws of Guthix in place of a Guthix staff. Not required for the Void set effect.

name: Void knight top
column2: Required for the Void set effect.

name: Void knight robe
column2: Required for the Void set effect.

name: Void knight gloves
column2: Required for the Void set effect.

name: Void mage helm
column2: One helmet is required for the Void set effect. +45% Magic accuracy.

name: Void ranger helm
column2: One helmet is required for the Void set effect. +10% Ranged accuracy and damage.

name: Void melee helm
column2: One helmet is required for the Void set effect. +10% Melee accuracy and damage.

name: Void seal
column2: Worn in the amulet slot. Operate in a Pest Control game to inflict 8-12 points of damage to surrounding pests.
